page.title: 17WILDLIFE
page.content: The ecology of our D-block varies from square to square.In square 51,28 there are a lot of houses where sparrows nest in gardens,there are small woods with many rabbits. In square 50,28 there is a {field study centre} where there are ponds, fields and woodland as well as a hut with equipment and facilities for study.By the banks of the river there are many species of bird including cormorants gulls and herons. The tree cover also varies.In square 50,28 there are a lot of oak and elm.By the river there are beeches and elm.Many elms have been destroyed because of {Dutch Elm Disease} . A dangerous plant called {Giant Hogweed} grows by the banks of the River Ribble.
